verbose_text: In BALB/3T3 cells overexpressing the human BRS-3 receptor, MK-5046 and the synthetic bombesin analogue, [D-Tyr 6, beta-Ala 11, Phe 13, Nle 14] bombesin 6-14, have shown high affinity for the receptor, and both compounds stimulate kinases involed in insulin signaling, such as p125 FAK, phosphorylated AKT (pAKT) and mitogen activated protein kinase (MAPK) phosphorylation.
evidence: insulin signaling, such as p125 FAK
